<h2 id="m-ocr">Processing of Image Data for Text Recognition (OCR)</h2>
<p>As part of our card scanner feature, we offer the ability to upload photos of collectible cards for automatic identification. In this process, cropped image sections (exclusively the bottom area of detected cards containing collector number and set information) are processed for automatic text recognition.</p>
<p>When five or more cards are detected in an image, the cropped image sections are transmitted to the Google Cloud Vision API for text recognition. When fewer than five cards are detected, text recognition is performed entirely locally in the user's browser using Tesseract.js, without any data being sent to external servers.</p>
<p>Through client-side image processing (canvas rendering), EXIF metadata (e.g., GPS coordinates or device information) is automatically removed before any transmission. The transmitted image sections are not permanently stored by Google but are processed only transiently for text recognition.</p>
<p>For cost control and abuse prevention, we log the use of the Google Vision API in our local database (timestamp, number of images processed, user ID). Image content is not stored.</p>
<ul class="m-elements">
<li><strong>Types of data processed:</strong> Image data (cropped card sections); Meta, communication, and procedural data (e.g., timestamps, number of images processed, user ID).</li>
<li><strong>Data subjects:</strong> Users (e.g., users of the card scanner feature).</li>
<li><strong>Purposes of processing:</strong> Automatic detection and identification of collectible cards to support collection management.</li>
<li><strong>Retention and deletion:</strong> Image data is not stored. API usage data is retained for cost control and removed upon account deletion.</li>
<li><strong>Legal bases:</strong> Consent (Art. 6 Abs. 1 S. 1 lit. a) DSGVO) – the user actively uploads images and initiates the processing.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Further information on processing operations, procedures, and services:</strong></p>
<ul class="m-elements">
<li><strong>Google Cloud Vision API: </strong>Text recognition (TEXT_DETECTION) on image sections of collectible cards; <strong>Service provider:</strong> Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland; <span class=""><strong>Legal bases:</strong> Consent (Art. 6 Abs. 1 S. 1 lit. a) DSGVO); </span><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://cloud.google.com/vision" target="_blank">https://cloud.google.com/vision</a>; <strong>Privacy policy:</strong> <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>; <strong>Basis for third-country transfers:</strong> Data Privacy Framework (DPF).</li>
</ul>

